PII GUARDIAN - FULL PROJECT DOCUMENTATION
Version: 1.0
Date: 2026-03-07
Repository Root: pii-guardian/

============================================================
1) PROJECT SUMMARY
============================================================
PII Guardian is an end-to-end privacy platform that detects, validates, and sanitizes sensitive data from structured and unstructured files. It supports role-based access control, secure encrypted storage, tamper-evident audit logs, malware reputation checks, risk analytics, and disaster-recovery backup export.

Primary goal:
- Prevent accidental leakage of personal/sensitive data.
- Provide secure sharing of sanitized outputs.
- Maintain auditability and compliance readiness.
                    
============================================================
2) PROBLEM STATEMENT
============================================================
Organizations receive mixed file types (PDF scans, documents, CSV/SQL dumps, screenshots, etc.). Manual PII removal is:
- slow,
- inconsistent,
- hard to verify,
- non-auditable.

PII Guardian automates the full lifecycle:
Upload -> Detection -> Validation -> Sanitization -> Secure Download -> Audit -> Risk Visibility.

============================================================
3) KEY CAPABILITIES
============================================================
A) Multi-format ingestion
- SQL, CSV, JSON, TXT
- PDF (digital + scanned)
- DOCX
- PNG/JPG/JPEG images
- Excel formats (XLS/XLSX/XLSM/XLTX/XLTM)

B) Detection pipeline
- Presidio Analyzer (NER + recognizers)
- Regex fallback recognizers
- Aadhaar checksum validation via Verhoeff
- Card-like checksum validation via Luhn
- Overlap resolution + entity priority logic
- Optional LLM-assisted extraction (config-driven)

C) OCR and non-text extraction
- PaddleOCR primary engine
- Tesseract fallback
- QR/barcode decoding with pyzbar
- Hindi + Gujarati OCR enabled via env config

D) Sanitization modes
- mask
- redact
- tokenize

E) Security and trust
- AES-GCM envelope encryption for originals at rest
- SHA-256 integrity checks (ciphertext + plaintext)
- Step-up password for sensitive downloads
- Binary signature blocking for executable uploads
- Optional VirusTotal hash reputation check with cache reuse
- Rate limiting + CORS allowlist + security headers

F) Governance and operations
- RBAC (admin/user)
- Tamper-evident audit logs (hash chain)
- SIEM-friendly audit export: CSV/JSON/JSONL
- Risk dashboard (overall, per-file, per-user, top entities)
- Backup ZIP export (DB dump + encrypted originals + manifest)

============================================================
